text: McKinley County is a county in the northwestern section of the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 72,902. Its county seat is Gallup. The county was created in 1901 and named for President William McKinley. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:1890s establishments in New Mexico Territory Category:1899 establishments in the United States
title: McKinley County, New Mexico
